T1  - On the term structure of interest rates and the risk of default: An analytical approach
AU  - Jonkhart, Marius J.L.
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 3
IS  - 3
SP  - 253
EP  - 262
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/09/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(79)90019-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426679900190
AB  - Students of the term structure of interest rates commonly assume the absence of the risk of default. This assumption severely limits the applicability of the results of the term structure theory in the field of corporate finance. In this paper it is explained how the risk of default could be incorporated into the well known unbiased expectations theory and how the resulting model is of direct use for a better understanding of interest rate risk differentials.
